{"id":9590,"date":"2024-01-26T09:38:49","date_gmt":"2024-01-26T04:08:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=9590"},"modified":"2023-04-26T22:44:54","modified_gmt":"2023-04-26T17:14:54","slug":"diy-furniture-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/diy-furniture-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"5 DIY Furniture Ideas That Add Vibrancy To Your Home"},"content":{"rendered":"<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Looking for creative furniture ideas for your compact Indian home? Here are 5 DIY furniture ideas to look at, peek inside.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&#8217;s crazy how expensive modern furniture can be! While ditching the overpriced furniture is not feasible for all, you can still take the DIY route to create an entertaining explorative space for you and your loved ones. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Besides, imagine how great you&#8217;d feel when your friends and family ask where that furniture is from.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DIY furniture is quite popular these days and an easier gamble with tons of resources available on the internet. Of course, they are no match for high-end, professionally built <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/\">interior solutions<\/a>. However, they are fun to give a try once in your life. So, here&#8217;s giving you 5 super fun and unique DIY furniture ideas for small spaces that you can easily create on the go. Without further ado, let&#8217;s dive right in.<\/span>\r\n<h2>Add DIY Bedroom Furniture Ideas With A Wooden Headboard<\/h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/wooden-headboard-designs\/\">Wooden headboards<\/a> are quite popular and add a rustic aesthetic to the space. Our first DIY furniture idea is this headboard that&#8217;s simple to design and yet expensive to look at. Complementing it is a matching side table.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All you need is light-coloured plywood and an old fruit crate. Drill or nail the plywood to the back of your bed that becomes a headboard, while an old fruit crate placed next to your bed acts as a side table. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Additionally, you can decorate the box with some candles, coffee mugs and miscellaneous items for subtle aesthetic warmth.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is an excellent DIY bedroom furniture idea for those who fancy <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/modern-rustic-interior-design\/\">rustic-style interiors<\/a> or want to add hints of this style to their otherwise dull bedroom.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>DIY Furniture Tip<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Add some freshness to the space with potted plants, fresh paint on the plywood and a hearty coat of varnish to eliminate splinters.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_44811\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-44811\" style=\"width: 940px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-44811 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221748\/DIY-bedroom-furniture-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"DIY Bedroom Furniture Ideas\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221748\/DIY-bedroom-furniture-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221748\/DIY-bedroom-furniture-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221748\/DIY-bedroom-furniture-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221748\/DIY-bedroom-furniture-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-44811\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A Headboard that&#8217;s swanky, stylish and affordable<\/figcaption><\/figure>\r\n<h2>A DIY Furniture Idea That Helps With Your Storage Problems<\/h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your hardware restoration goals just got a whole lot more achievable. If you want a unique shelf to make a statement to your living or dining area, here is our DIY furniture idea.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All you need is some wooden planks, adhesives, nails, and a drilling machine to get started. Collect decor pieces you want to display because this shelf will be ready in no time. The wooden planks are perfect as floating shelves and a sturdy companion for those who love books, decor and everything in between.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>DIY Furniture Tip: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sand the wooden planks and polish them with the wood touch you choose to give them a rustic vibe while protecting the wood.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_44810\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-44810\" style=\"width: 940px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-44810 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221741\/DIY-furniture-idea-with-storage.jpg\" alt=\"DIY Furniture Idea with storage\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221741\/DIY-furniture-idea-with-storage.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221741\/DIY-furniture-idea-with-storage-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221741\/DIY-furniture-idea-with-storage-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221741\/DIY-furniture-idea-with-storage-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-44810\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Floating shelves as the perfect storage and decor companion<\/figcaption><\/figure>\r\n<h2>A Unique DIY Furniture That&#8217;s Perfect For Your Brunch Space<\/h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A DIY furniture idea that sets a table of two for brunch? How cool is that? Here is what you need. Wooden crates, a cable spool, some wooden discs and a plyboard.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place the crates on the floor one topping another. You can also stick them together to make them sturdier. Place a plyboard behind this structure as shown in this image. Additionally, you can drill a wine rack into the plyboard to hang your glasses. For the table, look into cable spools and use it as a makeshift table for your brunch and coffee hours. If a spool isn&#8217;t easily accessible, you can attach two round wooden cutouts to a cylindrical base to make a spool table.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>DIY Furniture Tip: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Potted plants and biophilic decor bring life to a space. You can complement it with a crate. Buff it, followed with a paint or varnish of your choice, and you are good to go.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_44809\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-44809\" style=\"width: 940px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-44809 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221735\/DIY-furniture-for-brunch-space.jpg\" alt=\"DIY Furniture for brunch space\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221735\/DIY-furniture-for-brunch-space.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221735\/DIY-furniture-for-brunch-space-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221735\/DIY-furniture-for-brunch-space-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221735\/DIY-furniture-for-brunch-space-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-44809\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A unique brunch space as an escape from the mundane<\/figcaption><\/figure>\r\n<h2>A DIY Coffee Table And A Ladder Rack<\/h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A unique DIY furniture take on the coffee table design backed by a smart ladder rack to store your snacks and munchies! To give this cool DIY coffee table shape, you need four crates, two pipes or bamboo sticks and small wooden planks for the ladder rack.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place, drill or paste the back of all four crates to be accessible from each side, as shown in this image. You can use the open sides to stack magazines, books, TV remotes, pots and fruit baskets. The top can be used to place hot coffee mugs or cute decor.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coming to the ladder rack, paste or drill the planks between two pipes or bamboo sticks, forming a ladder. Keep your jars of snacks, cutlery and coffee mugs as shown in this image. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Additionally, the ladder rack can double as a bookshelf or a shelving space for additional storage. You can also choose to use it for displaying your decor elements, prized possessions or simply plants.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>DIY Furniture Tip<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Paint these DIY pieces in striking colours to bring a pop shock. Add fairy lights and indoor plants to make your space more appealing. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Or stick to neutral natural tones for a warm cosy visual appeal.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_44808\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-44808\" style=\"width: 940px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-44808 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221728\/DIY-coffee-table-and-a-ladder-rack.jpg\" alt=\"DIY Coffee Table And A Ladder Rack\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221728\/DIY-coffee-table-and-a-ladder-rack.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221728\/DIY-coffee-table-and-a-ladder-rack-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221728\/DIY-coffee-table-and-a-ladder-rack-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221728\/DIY-coffee-table-and-a-ladder-rack-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-44808\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A ladder shelf and coffee table for the industrial vibe with a touch of rustic charm<\/figcaption><\/figure>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also Read: <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/modern-coffee-table\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Modern Coffee Table Designs For Your Home<\/span><\/a>\r\n<h2>A DIY Furniture Idea That Brings Your Patio To Life<\/h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For the adventurous lot among you who have a knack for engineering, it&#8217;s time to get some work done! Design a unique yet comfortable settee for your patio or garden area. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You simply need some tyres, comfortable cushioning and tools to staple and drill, and some colours of your choice.\u00a0<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These kinds of seating are perfect for your patio or balcony space. You can also DIY these seats with wooden barrels if tyres aren&#8217;t easily accessible.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>DIY Furniture Tip: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Paint the tyres\/barrels before adding the cushions for a flawless finish. Get rid of old paint with the help of sandpaper. Use spray paint that contains primer to prevent your DIY furniture from rusting.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_44807\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-44807\" style=\"width: 940px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-44807 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221722\/DIY-furniture-idea-for-patio.jpg\" alt=\"DIY Furniture Idea for patio\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221722\/DIY-furniture-idea-for-patio.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221722\/DIY-furniture-idea-for-patio-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221722\/DIY-furniture-idea-for-patio-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/26221722\/DIY-furniture-idea-for-patio-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-44807\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Tyre DIY seats for a vibrant, fun patio space<\/figcaption><\/figure>\r\n\r\n<span data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:513,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;12&quot;:0}\"><div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Designer home interiors within your budget!\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/15153610\/designer-home-interiors-within-your-budget-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div><\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With these DIY furniture pieces, you can also consider designing a few decor pieces to complete the look. Here are some fun ideas to look into:<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>Flowering\/Plant Pots:<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Paint your old buckets with spray paint or acrylic colours.<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Next, drill a hole in the centre of the bucket&#8217;s base with a drill machine and it&#8217;s ready to use as a flower pot in your patio space.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>Serving Trays<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Use old handles from old wardrobes or almirahs and drill them onto each side of a softwood plank. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Additionally, you can try resin to create a glossy \/ glass effect and have a serving tray ready!<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>DIY Night Lamps Or Lanterns: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Take a balloon, yarn\/jute\/thick thread soaked in one part coloured water, and two-part glue. Wrap it around the balloon and leave it to dry. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Burst the balloon gently, and get the scraps out. Attach a bulb to the mould, and you are ready with a DIY lantern for your space!<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>A Pastry Jar Garden:<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Use old glass jars and mugs to replant your favourite herbs and place them in your living area or kitchen.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<b>Decorative Vases:<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Put those used alcohol and liquor bottles to some use by spray painting them. You can also try your hands decoupage to give it a vintage twist. These can be used as vases, decor pieces, and even water-propagated planters for your pothos.<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And with that, we end our super creative, fun DIY furniture ideas for your small home. Like these ideas? Try them out and <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/in.pinterest.com\/DC_designcafe\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">tag us on DesignCafe&#8217;s Pinterest account<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Loved the homes you see in the images above? <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Connect with our expert designers <\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">to design the home of your dreams today!<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Happy Decorating!<\/span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On the blog:\u00a0<\/span>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><a href=\"h